@selva-nexthop - currently, test_seq_idf_isolation only runs if there are T1 neighbors, since the feature is intended to add the no-export or withdraw route-maps towards T1. In your tests, it looks like you have T1 neighbors on UT2, which is causing this issue. By design, UT2 would have only LT2 as the downstream peer and not T1

In a disaggregated T2, these tests would run on LT2 which will not have the anchor route-maps that caused this issue.

The change made here (adding on-match-next) is a good fix, but the title of the PR is misleading. Could you please change this?

@liushilongbuaa Thanks for the link. The issue is specifically in the `sonic_config_engine` wheel build's pytest phase — the test `test_minigraph_packet_chassis_acl_local_host` triggers `asic_sensors_config.py` and `smartswitch_config.py` which call `get_path_to_platform_dir()` without guarding for missing platform. This raises `OSError` in build containers where no platform directory exists.

The daily pipeline might not hit this if it skips unit tests, uses cached wheels, or has specific platform environment variables set. Issue #20614 has multiple reporters.

I'll compare with the daily pipeline build logs and report back what I find.

@liushilongbuaa Thanks for the pointer to the daily VS pipeline! I compared its build against mine and I think the difference is likely the build parallelism level — the `get_path_to_platform_dir()` OSError surfaces during the `sonic_config_engine` wheel build when `CFGGEN_UNIT_TESTING` is cleared (set to empty string) by `test_minigraph_packet_chassis_acl_local_host`, which spawns a subprocess that calls `get_asic_sensors_config()` without a platform directory.

The issue was originally reported in #20614 by multiple users across different platforms (Marvell AMD64, VS ARM64, VS x86_64). It's a race condition in how the test clears `CFGGEN_UNIT_TESTING` — the subprocess inherits the empty value, bypasses the mock, and hits the real `get_path_to_platform_dir()` which fails inside the build container.

Could you try reproducing with a clean build at higher parallelism? The daily pipeline may use lower parallelism or a different test ordering that avoids the race. Happy to provide more specific reproduction steps if helpful.

